There should be an ymount utility.
This should have an fzf showing all available partitions in the system:
The preview window should show
Drive:
Partition:
Type:
Size:
Used space: x GB
Free space: x GB

Mount point: <not set>  or <$HOME/Drives/xxx>

Selecting the drive should open an fzf with:

- "Set mount point" if not set or "Change mount point" if set.
- Mount if not mounted "Unmount" if mounted
- back
